<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-606] InformixDictionary default setting beaks many testcases</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-606</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In testing Informix backend store,  there are many query test string failed:&lt;br/&gt;
1. parameter of a boolean value does not work, should use &apos;t for true, &apos;f&apos; for false&lt;br/&gt;
 WHERE (t1.isManager = ?) &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;params=(boolean) false&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   should generate  WHERE (t1.isManager = ?) &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;params=(String) f&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT(t1.name)) reported  syntax error  &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;code=-201, state=42000&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    should generate COUNT(DISTINCT t1.name ) &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3. CROSS JOIN syntax error &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    should generate JOIN with ON 1 = 1&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;4. There is no equivalent  function for LOCATE.  Informix users must create INSTR as a user defined function.  &lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;3. CONCAT function in &apos;||&apos; does not take parameter markers&lt;br/&gt;
  WHERE ((?||t0.name) LIKE ? ESCAPE &apos;\&apos;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  should generate  CONCAT(?, t0.name)&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
